channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "My picture on tinder is me riding a carousel, and almost every single guy says something about the fact that I'm an excellent stunt pony rider, or I'm really good riding a horse, and it's so stupid. This guy asked where it was, and I said it was taken at Magic Mountain. He sent me a long message with lots of questions. So I'm going to message this guy back a curt answer, not answering all of his questions. But as far as dates go, that's all I have pending for tinder. I have other dates. Tell us about the others. So okay, the second guy I have to cancel on for tonight, we'll call him Jay. I think I told you about him yesterday. This is, no, no, no, no, I haven't told you about this guy. So Jay is a friend of my friend Abby's boyfriend Pete, and she's been trying to hook me up with him. And we were going to do the day date thing at a hike in Temescal, because they all live out in Santa Monica, but I flaked on this guy already twice, and so I feel kind of bad. I might invite him to Porvoo too. So I do this. So if they both show up, it usually doesn't happen this way, but there's a possibility that it can. So this is what I'll do. If I have to flake on a guy and I feel bad about it, I'll try to make it okay so he doesn't ask me. I'll say, I'll kind of try to flip it and be like, well, you can come meet up with us, and then he'll have to tell me no, so he was the last one that said no. So I'm not in the doghouse that way.
